#         "input,output\nWhat should I do during an earthquake?,\"During an earthquake, drop, cover, and hold on. Get under sturdy furniture, cover your head and neck, and stay indoors until the shaking stops. Avoid windows and heavy objects that might fall.\"\nWhat are the most common natural disasters in India?,\"The most common natural disasters in India include floods, cyclones, earthquakes, landslides, and droughts. These events cause significant damage and require preparedness.\"\nHow can I protect myself during a flood?,\"During a flood, move to higher ground immediately. Avoid walking or driving through floodwaters. If trapped, go to the roof and signal for help. Stay informed through weather updates and local authorities.\"\nWhat is the National Disaster Management Authority (NDMA)?,\"The NDMA is an Indian government agency responsible for disaster management. It formulates policies, plans, and guidelines for disaster management and coordinates response and relief efforts.\"\nWhat are the emergency helpline numbers for disaster relief in India?,\"The National Emergency Helpline number is 112. You can also contact the National Disaster Response Force (NDRF) at 1078 or 011-23438085. For specific state helplines, please refer to local government resources.\"\nHow can I contact NGOs that help during disasters in India?,\"You can contact NGOs like the Indian Red Cross Society, Goonj, SEEDS India, and Care India for disaster relief assistance. Many of these organizations have helplines and websites for donations and volunteering.\"\nWhat are the protection strategies for a cyclone?,\"Before a cyclone, secure your home, stay indoors, and keep emergency supplies ready. Follow evacuation orders if issued. During the cyclone, stay in a safe room, away from windows, and listen to updates from authorities.\"\nHow can I help during a disaster?,\"You can help by donating to trusted NGOs, volunteering with relief organizations, spreading awareness, and ensuring your own safety so that you can assist others effectively. Check with local authorities on how to contribute safely.\"\nWhat are the effects of drought in India?,\"Droughts in India lead to water scarcity, crop failure, and livestock loss. They affect millions of people, particularly in rural areas. Effective water management, rainwater harvesting, and drought-resistant crops are critical solutions.\"\nWhat safety measures should I take for landslides?,\"For landslides, stay away from slopes during heavy rains. If you live in a landslide-prone area, create barriers and plant vegetation to stabilize the soil. If a landslide occurs, evacuate immediately and avoid riverbanks and valleys.\"\nWhat are the steps to prepare for a heatwave in India?,\"To prepare for a heatwave, stay hydrated, avoid going out during peak heat hours, wear light-colored, loose-fitting clothing, and keep your home cool by using fans, curtains, and ventilation. Keep an eye on weather updates and plan your activities accordingly.\"\nHow can I help prevent wildfires in India?,\"To prevent wildfires, avoid lighting fires in forested areas, dispose of cigarettes properly, and clear dry leaves and flammable materials from around your home. Report any signs of fire to local authorities immediately.\"\nWhat should I include in a disaster emergency kit?,\"A disaster emergency kit should include water, non-perishable food, a flashlight, extra batteries, a first-aid kit, essential medications, identification documents, cash, and a battery-powered radio. Customize your kit based on the specific disaster risks in your area.\"\nWhat are the flood-prone areas in India?,\"lood-prone areas in India include the states of Assam, Bihar, Uttar Pradesh, West Bengal, and parts of Maharashtra and Kerala. These regions often experience heavy monsoon rains that can lead to severe flooding.\"\nHow do I protect my livestock during a flood?,\"During a flood, move your livestock to higher ground or a safe shelter. Ensure they have enough food and water stored in advance. Keep vaccination records and essential medicines handy. Stay informed through local agricultural departments.\"\nWhat role does the Indian Meteorological Department (IMD) play in disaster management?,\"The IMD provides weather forecasts, early warnings, and alerts for various natural disasters, including cyclones, floods, and heatwaves. Their timely updates help authorities and citizens take preventive measures and stay prepared.\"\nWhat was the impact of the 2001 Gujarat earthquake?,\"The 2001 Gujarat earthquake, with a magnitude of 7.7, caused widespread destruction, killing over 20,000 people and leaving thousands homeless. The disaster highlighted the need for better building codes and disaster preparedness in earthquake-prone areas.\"\nHow can I stay informed during a cyclone in India?,\"During a cyclone, stay informed through local news channels, the Indian Meteorological Department's website, and official government apps like the NDMA app. Listen to updates from authorities and follow any evacuation orders promptly.\"\nHow can schools in India prepare for disasters?,\"Schools can prepare for disasters by conducting regular drills, educating students about safety measures, creating evacuation plans, and ensuring that buildings are structurally sound. Schools should also have emergency kits and first-aid supplies on hand.\"\nWhat are some famous NGOs in India that assist during natural disasters?,\"Some well-known NGOs in India that assist during natural disasters include Goonj, SEEDS India, Save the Children India, and Oxfam India. These organizations provide relief supplies, shelter, medical aid, and rehabilitation support to affected communities.\"\n\"The power is out due to the cyclone, and I can't charge my phone. What should I do?\",Conserve your phone's battery by turning off unnecessary apps and features. Use a portable power bank if available. Prioritize emergency calls and messages.\nWe only have limited food during this flood. What should we eat first?,\"Prioritize perishable items like fruits, vegetables, and dairy products. Save non-perishable items like canned goods and dry foods for later.\"\n\"The floodwaters are rising, and we're trapped on the second floor. What should we do?\",\"Move to the highest safe point in your home, like the roof. Signal for help using bright cloth or a flashlight. Avoid wading through floodwaters unless absolutely necessary.\"\nIâ€™m in an earthquake-prone area. What should I do when the shaking starts?,\"Drop, cover, and hold on. Get under sturdy furniture like a table, and protect your head and neck. Stay away from windows and heavy objects that might fall.\"\n\"The roads are blocked due to the landslide, and we canâ€™t leave. What should we do?\",\"Stay indoors and away from slopes. Listen to local authorities for updates. Prepare for potential evacuation, but only leave if it's safe and instructed.\"\nIâ€™m running low on clean water during this cyclone. How can I purify water?,\"Boil water for at least one minute to kill harmful bacteria. If boiling isn't possible, use water purification tablets or add a few drops of bleach to clear water.\"\n\"Weâ€™re trapped in a building after the earthquake, and the exits are blocked. What now?\",Stay calm and signal for help using a whistle or tapping. Avoid using open flames due to possible gas leaks. Try to find a safe spot under sturdy furniture.\n\"Thereâ€™s a cyclone warning, and we live in a low-lying area. What should we do?\",\"Evacuate to higher ground as soon as possible. Take essential supplies like water, food, and medications. Inform neighbors and local authorities of your evacuation.\"\n\"The tsunami alert has been issued, and we are close to the shore. What should we do?\",Immediately move to higher ground or inland. Do not wait for official orders if you feel the ground shaking or see unusual ocean activity.\nOur area is at risk of landslides. How can we prepare our home?,Ensure proper drainage around your home and reinforce retaining walls. Keep emergency supplies ready and listen to weather updates to evacuate if necessary.\n\"The earthquake has stopped, but there are aftershocks. Should we stay outside?\",\"Yes, stay outside in an open area away from buildings and power lines. Aftershocks can cause additional damage, so avoid re-entering buildings until theyâ€™re declared safe.\"\n\"Weâ€™re stranded due to the cyclone, and thereâ€™s no sign of rescuers. How can we signal for help?\",\"Use brightly colored cloth or reflective materials to signal from a visible location. If you have a flashlight, signal in intervals to attract attention.\"\nThereâ€™s a severe food shortage in the flood. Whatâ€™s the best way to manage the remaining food?,\"Ration the food by dividing it into small portions. Focus on high-energy foods like nuts, dried fruits, and canned goods that require minimal preparation.\"\nWater is contaminated due to the flood. How can I make it safe to drink?,\"Boil water if possible. If not, use a water filter or purification tablets. In extreme cases, use bleachâ€”add 8 drops of bleach per gallon of clear water.\"\nOur shelter is damaged after the earthquake. Where can we find safe shelter?,\"Look for local evacuation centers or schools. If youâ€™re outside, stay in open areas away from trees, buildings, and power lines.\"\n\"We have no access to medical help, and someone is injured. What basic first aid can we provide?\",\"Stop any bleeding by applying pressure with a clean cloth. Clean wounds with purified water. Immobilize broken limbs with makeshift splints, and keep the person warm.\"\n\"The power is out, and we canâ€™t contact anyone. How can we stay informed during the cyclone?\",Use a battery-powered or hand-crank radio to listen to weather updates and official instructions. Conserve your phone battery for emergency calls\nThe landslide blocked the road to our home. How can we clear it safely?,Do not attempt to clear the road yourself if there is still danger of more landslides. Wait for professional help and stay in a safe location.\nWeâ€™ve run out of fuel for cooking during this flood. What alternative methods can we use?,\"If possible, use a portable camping stove or grill outside. If youâ€™re indoors, focus on foods that donâ€™t require cooking, like canned goods and dried fruits.\"\nThe cyclone caused structural damage to our home. How can we secure it temporarily?,Use tarps or plastic sheets to cover exposed areas. Reinforce weak spots with wooden planks or other available materials. Avoid staying in severely damaged areas.\nI need help with food supplies.,\"Please provide your location, the quantity of food needed, and any special requirements. Your request will be sent to the relevant NGO and government authorities.\"\nMy house is flooded. What should I do?,\"Register your query in the app,We will send your location and a request for immediate assistance to the government and NGOs. You will receive updates on the status of your request by connecting the NGOs and the rescue teams.\"\nCan I get medical aid?,Please enter your location and describe the medical aid you need. This information will be forwarded to emergency services and relevant organizations.\nHow can I report a damaged road?,Use the 'Report an Issue' feature to provide details about the road damage and your location. This will alert the authorities to address the issue promptly.\nI need shelter. How do I request it?,\"Specify your location, the number of people needing shelter, and any special requirements. Your request will be sent to local shelters and emergency services.\"\nWhat resources are available in my area?,View the map to see available resources in your area. You can also request specific resources if needed.\nI can't contact emergency services. What should I do?,\"You can report the issue through the app, and we will notify emergency services and provide you with alternative contact methods.\"\nI need to report a missing person,\"Please provide details about the missing person, your location, and any other relevant information. We will forward this to authorities and NGOs.\"\nHow do I update my resource request?,You can update your request by accessing the 'Resource Request' section in the app and modifying the details as needed.\nWhere can I find local aid centers?,Use the map feature to locate nearby aid centers and shelters. You can also request additional information through the app.\nIs there any update on my request for medical supplies?,Check the 'Request Status' section in the app for real-time updates on your request. You will also receive notifications about the status\nHow do I send my location for immediate help?,Use the 'Send Location' feature to automatically share your current location with emergency services and NGOs.\nI need to contact a local NGO. How can I do that?,Find contact information for local NGOs through the app and directly reach out to them for assistance.\nCan I see the status of other reported issues?,The app provides updates on reported issues. Check the 'Status Updates' section for information on ongoing situations.\nWhat should I include in my resource request?,\"Include details such as the type of resource needed, quantity, location, and any specific requirements. This will help in processing your request efficiently.\"\nHow will I know if my issue report is received?,You will receive a confirmation message and updates on the status of your report through the app.\nWhat if I need urgent help but can't access the app?,\"Try to reach out to local emergency services directly. If you can access the app later, you can report the situation and request additional help\"\nCan I track the progress of resource distribution?,\"Yes, you can track the progress through the app's 'Resource Tracking' feature, which provides updates on the status of your request.\"\nHow do I report a technical issue with the app?,Use the 'Report Technical Issue' feature to provide details about the problem. Our support team will address it as soon as possible.\nWill I receive updates if the situation changes?,\"Yes, the app will provide real-time updates on the situation, including any changes or new developments related to your request.\"\nWhich regions in Tamil Nadu are prone to earthquakes?,\"The Nilgiris, Coimbatore, and Salem districts are considered earthquake-prone areas in Tamil Nadu.\"\nAre there any specific areas in Tamil Nadu that are vulnerable to landslides?,\"The Western Ghats, Nilgiris, and Anaimalai hills are particularly susceptible to landslides due to their hilly terrain and heavy rainfall.\"\nWhat steps should I take to prepare for a cyclone?,\"To prepare for a cyclone, secure windows and doors, stock up on essential supplies like food and water, have an emergency kit ready, and follow local weather updates.\"\nHow can I protect my home from floods?,\"To protect your home from floods, elevate electrical appliances, seal any cracks in walls and floors, and create barriers with sandbags if necessary. Also, know your evacuation routes.\"\nWhat are the best practices for earthquake preparedness?,\"Practice 'Drop, Cover, and Hold On' drills, secure heavy furniture, create an emergency plan, and know how to turn off utilities in case of damage.\"\nWhat should I include in a disaster emergency kit?,\"Include items like non-perishable food, water, first aid supplies, a flashlight, batteries, a multi-tool, important documents, and medications\"\nHow can I stay safe during a flood?,\"Avoid walking or driving through floodwaters, move to higher ground, and listen to official warnings. If trapped, call emergency services for help\"\nWhat are the common disaster risks in Tamil Nadu?,\"Tamil Nadu is prone to cyclones, floods, and earthquakes. Areas near the coast and riverbanks are particularly vulnerable.\"\nHow can I help mitigate the effects of a tsunami?,\"Follow tsunami evacuation routes, move to higher ground immediately, and stay away from the coast until authorities declare it safe.\"\nWhat should I do if there's a severe heatwave?,\"Stay hydrated, avoid outdoor activities during peak heat hours, use fans or air conditioning, and wear lightweight clothing.\"\nHow can I ensure my family is prepared for a natural disaster?,\"Create a family emergency plan, conduct regular drills, prepare an emergency kit, and stay informed about potential hazards in your area.\"\nWhat are the safety measures for a chemical spill?,\"vacuate the area immediately, avoid inhaling fumes, follow local evacuation orders, and report the incident to authorities.\"\nWhere are the disaster-prone areas in Chennai?,\"Areas in Chennai prone to flooding include low-lying regions and those near water bodies. Coastal areas are also at risk during cyclones.Especially Areas in Chennai prone to flooding include low-lying regions and those near water bodies. Coastal areas are also at risk during cyclones.Adambakkam, Velachery, Madipakkam, Sholinganallur, Perumbakkam.Adyar River basin, Cooum River basin, Pallikaranai marsh, Porur lake\"\nHow can I prevent damage from a wildfire?,\"Create defensible space around your property, remove flammable materials, and have an evacuation plan in place.\"\nWhat should I do if I receive a tsunami warning?,\"Immediately move to higher ground, follow evacuation routes, and stay tuned to official updates for further instructions.\"\nWhat are the best ways to secure a building before a cyclone?,\"Reinforce roof and window structures, trim trees near the house, and ensure that the building's foundation is stable.\"\nHow can I find safe evacuation routes during a flood?,Check with local authorities for designated evacuation routes and stay updated through official channels for any changes\nWhat are the key elements of a disaster response plan?,\"A disaster response plan should include emergency contacts, evacuation routes, roles and responsibilities, and communication strategies.\"\nWhat safety measures should I take during a tornado?,\"Seek shelter in a basement or interior room, avoid windows, and stay informed through weather alerts and updates.\"\nHow can I prepare my business for a natural disaster?,\"Develop a business continuity plan, secure critical data, train employees on emergency procedures, and review insurance coverage.\"\nWhat should I do if I'm caught in a landslide?,\"Move to higher ground as quickly as possible, avoid areas with loose debris, and seek shelter if you cannot evacuate immediately.\"\nWhere can I find resources for disaster preparedness in Tamil Nadu?,Tamil Naduâ€™s disaster management is overseen by the State Disaster Management Authority and District Disaster Management Authorities. The Tsunami Early Warning Center also plays a crucial role in providing early warnings for tsunamis. These authorities work together to ensure effective disaster management and response in the state.\nWhat are the early warning signs of an earthquake?,There are often no early warning signs for earthquakes. Stay prepared by securing your home and having an emergency plan in place.\nHow can I protect my crops from extreme weather events?,\"Use protective coverings, improve soil drainage, and select crops that are resilient to extreme weather conditions.\"\nWhat should I do if a volcanic eruption is imminent?,\"Follow evacuation orders, protect yourself from ash fallout, and stay indoors with windows and doors closed\"\nHow can I keep my pets safe during a disaster?,\"Include pets in your emergency plan, have a pet emergency kit ready, and ensure they have identification tags and microchips.\"\nWhat are the common natural disaster risks in Coimbatore?,\"Coimbatore is at risk of floods, especially during heavy monsoon rains. It may also experience occasional earthquakes and heatwaves.\"\nHow can I prepare for a hurricane if I live near the coast?,\"Reinforce your home, have a hurricane emergency kit, and plan for evacuation if necessary. Stay informed about storm forecasts.\"\nWhat should I do if there's a risk of landslides in my area?,\"Avoid areas prone to landslides, ensure proper drainage around your property, and stay informed about weather conditions\"\nHow can I create a family emergency contact list?,\"Include contact information for all family members, neighbors, and emergency services. Make sure everyone has a copy and knows how to use it.\"\nWhat are the preventive measures for drought,\"Conserve water, use drought-resistant plants, and implement water-saving techniques in daily life.\"\nWhat should I do if I'm stranded during a disaster?,\"Stay in a safe location, use emergency communication methods to reach help, and conserve your resources until assistance arrives.\"\nHow can I ensure my community is prepared for natural disasters?,\"Organize community meetings, share preparedness information, conduct drills, and collaborate with local authorities.\"\nWhat are the specific disaster risks in the Nilgiris district?,\"The Nilgiris district is prone to landslides, heavy rainfall, and occasional flooding. Be aware of weather warnings and take necessary precautions\"\nHow can I secure my property from storm damage?,\"Strengthen roof structures, install storm shutters, and ensure proper drainage around your property.\"\nWhat safety tips should I follow during a severe thunderstorm?,\"Avoid using electrical appliances, stay indoors away from windows, and seek shelter in a low-lying area if necessary.\"\nHow can I prepare for a pandemic-related disaster?,\"Follow health guidelines, stock up on essential supplies, maintain good hygiene, and stay informed about updates from health authorities.\"\nWhat are the safety measures for industrial accidents?,\"Ensure proper safety training, follow protocols for handling hazardous materials, and have an emergency response plan in place.\"\nHow can I stay informed about disaster risks in my area?,\"Subscribe to local alerts, follow news updates, and use disaster management apps for real-time information\"\nWhat should I do if there's a risk of flooding in my area?,\"Monitor weather forecasts, avoid low-lying areas, and prepare an evacuation plan in case flooding becomes severe.\"\nHow can I contribute to disaster relief efforts?,\"Donate to reputable organizations, volunteer your time, and support local disaster relief initiatives.\"\nWhat are the emergency procedures for a gas leak?,\"Evacuate the area immediately, avoid using electrical devices, and contact emergency services to handle the situation.\"\nWhat are the signs of an impending cyclone in Tamil Nadu?,\"Cyclone warnings are often indicated by hoisting signal flags at ports, increased cloud cover, strong winds, and changes in sea conditions. Fishermen should avoid going out to sea when these signs are observed.\"\nHow can I recognize an approaching earthquake?,\"ommon signs include minor tremors, sudden animal behavior changes, and unusual noises. However, earthquakes are difficult to predict with certainty, so maintaining preparedness is crucial.\"\nWhat visual signals indicate severe weather conditions?,\"Severe weather can be indicated by darkening skies, rapid changes in wind speed, and the appearance of a greenish or yellowish hue in the sky, especially before a storm.\"\nWhat are the warning signs of a flood in my area?,\"Early signs include rising water levels, rapid accumulation of water in streets, and warnings from local authorities. Be alert to changes in local river or drainage conditions.\"\nHow are tsunami warnings communicated?,\"Tsunami warnings are communicated through sirens, emergency alerts on TV and radio, and evacuation orders. Coastal areas should monitor these warnings closely and move to higher ground if necessary\"\nWhat are the indicators of a heatwave?,\"Indicators include prolonged periods of high temperatures, unusually high humidity levels, and heat advisories from meteorological agencies. It's important to stay hydrated and avoid excessive outdoor activities.\"\nWhat are the signs of an approaching tornado?,\"Signs include a dark, low-lying, and greenish-colored sky, a loud, continuous roar or rumble, and the sight of a rotating, horizontal cloud base. Seek shelter immediately if these signs are observed.\"\nWhat are the warning signs of a landslide?,\"Signs include ground cracks, unusual rockfalls, and changes in water flow patterns. Heavy rainfall can trigger landslides, so be alert to weather forecasts and warnings.\"\nHow are cyclone severity levels communicated at ports?,\"Cyclone severity is communicated using signal flags. For example, a red flag with a black circle indicates a cyclone alert, while a combination of flags can signify the severity level.\"\nWhat should I look for to detect a drought?,\"Signs of a drought include persistent lack of rainfall, reduced water levels in rivers and lakes, and visible impacts on vegetation and crops. Water conservation measures should be adopted.\"\n\"What are the signs of an approaching storm surge?\"\"\",\"Storm surge signs include rising sea levels, strong coastal winds, and sudden changes in tide patterns. Coastal areas should prepare for potential flooding and follow evacuation orders.\"\nHow can I identify early signs of a hailstorm?,\"Early signs include dark, stormy clouds with a yellow or greenish tint and sudden drops in temperature. Hailstorms can cause significant damage, so take shelter indoors\"\nWhat are the indicators of a severe thunderstorm?,\"Indicators include intense lightning, strong winds, large hailstones, and heavy rain. Pay attention to weather alerts and seek shelter in a safe location.\"\nHow are extreme cold weather conditions signaled?,\"Extreme cold weather is usually signaled by frost advisories, severe weather warnings, and noticeable drops in temperature. Prepare by dressing warmly and protecting pipes from freezing.\"\nWhat are the warning signs of a chemical spill?,\"Warning signs include unusual chemical smells, changes in air quality, and visible spills or leaks. Follow safety protocols and evacuate if necessary.\"\nWhat are the signs of a wildfire approaching?,\"Signs include smoke in the air, unusual fire behavior, and changes in local wind patterns. Be prepared to evacuate if necessary and follow local fire alerts.\"\nHow are alerts for high winds communicated?,\"Alerts for high winds are communicated through weather warnings, strong wind advisories, and changes in local wind speeds. Secure outdoor items and stay indoors during high wind events\"\nWhat are the signs of a major road accident or industrial disaster?,\"Signs include unusual noises, smoke, or fire. In case of an industrial disaster, follow emergency protocols and stay away from the affected area.\"\nWhat are the signs of an imminent landslide in hilly areas?,\"Look for ground cracks, increased soil movement, and changes in water flow. Heavy rains and seismic activity can trigger landslides in these areas.\"\nHow can I detect the early signs of a flood in low-lying areas?,\"Early signs include rapid water level rise, pooling in streets, and heavy rainfall. Prepare for evacuation and monitor weather alerts closely\"\nHow can I recognize signs of extreme weather in coastal regions?,\"Look for increased wave activity, rapid changes in wind direction, and rising sea levels. Coastal areas should heed storm warnings and prepare for potential flooding.\"\nWhat does one cone hoisted at a port in Tamil Nadu indicate?,One cone hoisted at a port in Tamil Nadu indicates that a distant cyclone may affect the region. Fishermen are advised to stay cautious and avoid venturing too far out to sea.\nWhat does two cones hoisted at a port signify?,\"Two cones hoisted indicate that a cyclone is approaching and is likely to affect the coastal area. All marine operations should cease, and vessels should return to port.\"\nWhat does three cones hoisted at a Tamil Nadu port mean?,\"Three cones hoisted signal that a severe cyclone is imminent, and the port is under threat. Complete evacuation of the coastline and port areas is recommended.\"\nHow do four cones hoisted at a port warn about cyclones?,Four cones hoisted at a port indicate that a very severe cyclone is approaching. This warning requires immediate and complete evacuation from coastal areas and shutting down all port activities.\nWhat is indicated by a cone with a black flag hoisted at the port?,\"A cone with a black flag indicates that a cyclone has developed and is expected to strike the coast. All activities should be halted, and people should seek shelter.\"\nWhat does a signal with two cones and a black flag represent?,\"Two cones with a black flag indicate that a severe cyclone is approaching, and itâ€™s expected to cross the coast. Immediate evacuation and disaster preparedness actions should be taken.\"\nWhat does a cage hoisted with a red flag at a port mean?,A cage hoisted with a red flag signifies that a very dangerous cyclone is expected to hit the coast soon. Itâ€™s a critical alert for people to evacuate and for authorities to implement emergency protocols.\nWhat should fishermen do if two black flags are hoisted at the port?,\"Two black flags indicate an extremely severe cyclone warning. Fishermen must avoid going to sea, and those already at sea should return immediately. All emergency precautions should be in place.\"\nHow is a cyclone alert conveyed with a combination of one cone and one black flag?,\"One cone and one black flag indicate that a cyclone is in the vicinity, and the situation is dangerous. Coastal residents and fishermen should be on high alert and prepare for possible evacuation.\"\nWhat does a cage hoisted with two black flags and a red flag indicate?,\"This combination signifies a super cyclone warning. Immediate evacuation is mandatory, and all emergency response teams should be activated\"\nHow is a cyclone warning updated as it intensifies?,\"As a cyclone intensifies, ports will i